# WHAT IT IS
#   filecoin-pin is the official Filecoin Foundation reference
#   implementation of the IPFS Pinning Service API
#   (https://ipfs.github.io/pinning-services-api-spec/) backed by
#   Filecoin's PDP (Proof of Data Possession) service via the
#   `@filoz/synapse-sdk`.  Run `filecoin-pin server` and you get
#   a standards-compliant pinning service that, instead of
#   replicating to a private cluster, plumbs the IPFS Bitswap
#   ingest pipeline through into Filecoin storage providers,
#   pays them in USDFC over Filecoin Pay, and retrieves blocks
#   back through the same Bitswap link when a client requests
#   them.  Underneath it stands a full Helia 6.x JS-IPFS node
#   running TCP + Yamux + Noise + Identify on a libp2p 3.x
#   stack, with `@helia/unixfs` mounting UnixFS DAGs and
#   `@helia/block-brokers` mediating the Bitswap session.
#
#   The CLI is a commander.js multi-command driver that exposes
#   server-mode, on-chain payment management, data-set lifecycle,
#   add/remove operations, provider inspection, and session-key
#   authorization sub-commands.  The on-chain side is driven via
#   viem against Filecoin's FVM so the same binary works as a
#   pinning daemon AND as the operator's day-to-day fleet
#   management tool.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.ts + src/commands/
#                       {server,payments,data-set,import,add,rm,
#                       provider,session}.ts commander.js
#                       declarations; extracted via `gh api
#                       repos/filecoin-project/filecoin-pin/
#                       contents/src/...`)
#
#   filecoin-pin [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options:
#     -v, --verbose                  Verbose output
#     --no-update-check              Skip check for npm registry
#                                    updates
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
#   Subcommands:
#     server [OPTIONS]               Start the IPFS Pinning
#                                    Service API server
#       -p, --port <N>                 Server port  [default: 3000]
#       --host <HOST>                  Server host  [default:
#                                      127.0.0.1]
#       --car-storage <PATH>           Path for CAR file storage
#                                      [default: ./cars]
#       --database <PATH>              Path to SQLite database
#                                      [default: ./pins.db]
#       --private-key <KEY>            Private key for Synapse
#                                      (env: PRIVATE_KEY)
#       --wallet-address <ADDR>        Wallet address for session
#                                      key auth (env:
#                                      WALLET_ADDRESS)
#       --session-key <KEY>            Session key for session
#                                      key auth (env: SESSION_KEY)
#       --access-token <TOKEN>         Bearer token required on
#                                      all API requests except
#                                      GET / (env: ACCESS_TOKEN)
#
#     payments [SUBCMD]              Manage payment setup for
#                                    Filecoin Onchain Cloud
#       setup [--auto] [...]           Setup payment approvals
#         --auto                         Run in automatic mode
#                                        with defaults
#       fund [--days <N>] [--amount <USDFC>] [...]
#                                      Adjust funds to an exact
#                                      runway (days) or total
#                                      deposit
#         --days <N>                     Set final runway to N
#                                        days
#         --amount <USDFC>               Set final deposited
#                                        total to N USDFC
#       withdraw                       Withdraw funds from
#                                      Filecoin Pay to your
#                                      wallet
#       status [--include-rails]       Check current payment
#                                      setup status
#         --include-rails                Show payment rail
#                                        details
#       deposit [--amount <USDFC>] [--days <N>]
#                                      Deposit or top-up funds in
#                                      Filecoin Pay
#
#     data-set [SUBCMD]              Inspect data sets managed
#                                    through Filecoin Onchain
#                                    Cloud  (alias: dataset)
#       show <DATA_SET_ID>             Display detailed info for
#                                      a data set
#       list [--all] [--provider-id <ID>]
#                                      List all data sets for the
#                                      account  (alias: ls)
#         --all                          Show all data sets, not
#                                        just the ones created
#                                        with filecoin-pin
#         --provider-id <ID>             Filter data sets by
#                                        provider ID
#       terminate <DATA_SET_ID> [--wait]
#                                      Terminate a data set and
#                                      associated payment rails
#         --wait                         Wait for the termination
#                                        transaction to be
#                                        confirmed
#
#     import <FILE> [--copies <N>]   Import an existing CAR file
#                                    to Filecoin via Synapse
#       --copies <N>                   Number of storage copies
#                                      to create  [default: 2]
#
#     add <PATH> [--copies <N>]      Add a file or directory to
#                                    Filecoin via Synapse
#                                    (creates a UnixFS CAR)
#       --copies <N>                   Number of storage copies
#                                      to create  [default: 2]
#
#     rm [OPTIONS]                   Remove piece(s) from a
#                                    DataSet
#       --wait-for-confirmation        Wait for transaction
#                                      confirmation before
#                                      exiting
#       --force                        Skip confirmation prompt
#                                      when using --all
#
#     provider [SUBCMD]              Inspect and interact with
#                                    storage providers
#       list [--all] [--endorsed]      List providers  (alias: ls)
#         --all                          List all active providers
#                                        (ignoring approval)
#         --endorsed                     List only endorsed
#                                        providers
#       show <PROVIDER>                Show details for a specific
#                                      provider
#       ping [<PROVIDER>] [--all]      Ping provider PDP service
#                                      (pings all approved
#                                      providers if no ID)
#         --all                          Ping all active providers
#
#     session [SUBCMD]               Session-key lifecycle
#       create [--validity-days <N>] [--session-key <KEY>]
#                                      Generate (or reuse) a
#                                      session key and authorize
#                                      it on-chain
#         --validity-days <N>            Number of days the
#                                        session key should be
#                                        valid  (max 365,
#                                        default 10)
#         --session-key <KEY>            Reuse an existing session
#                                        private key (can also
#                                        use SESSION_KEY env)
#       authorize <SESSION_ADDRESS> [--validity-days <N>]
#                                      Authorize an externally
#                                      generated session address
#                                      on-chain  (two-party flow)
#         --validity-days <N>            Number of days the
#                                        authorization is valid
#                                        (max 365, default 10)
#       generate                       Generate a session keypair
#                                      locally  (no chain
#                                      interaction; consumer side
#                                      of the two-party flow)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `libp2p ^3.2.2` + `helia ^6.1.4` +
#   `@helia/unixfs ^7.0.4` + `@helia/block-brokers ^5.1.3` +
#   `@libp2p/identify ^4.1.2` + `@libp2p/tcp ^11.0.17` +
#   `@chainsafe/libp2p-noise ^17.0.0` + `@chainsafe/libp2p-yamux
#   ^8.0.1` declared in package.json — `libp2p` and `helia` are
#   THE canonical JavaScript P2P + IPFS stack, maintained by
#   the libp2p / IPFS / Helia / Protocol Labs / ChainSafe
#   community (ipfs/helia + libp2p/js-libp2p, the modern
#   js-libp2p 3.x rewrite that replaced the legacy js-ipfs
#   implementation — used by ProbeLab, Filecoin Foundation,
#   ipfs/service-worker-gateway, brave-ios, Glimesh streaming,
#   ZeroNet-V2, Hardhat-IPFS plugin, the Brave browser's
#   integrated IPFS support, and dozens of pinning service
#   implementations).  `libp2p` exposes the typed
#   `createLibp2p({transports, streamMuxers, connectionEncrypters,
#   peerDiscovery, services, addresses: {listen, announce},
#   peerId, datastore, connectionManager, connectionGater,
#   logger, metrics, nodeInfo, privateKey, start, transports
#   ManageAfterStop, ...})` factory returning a typed
#   `Libp2p` node with `node.start()` / `node.stop()` /
#   `node.dial(multiaddr)` / `node.dialProtocol(peer, protocol)`
#   / `node.hangUp(peer)` / `node.handle(protocol, handler)` /
#   `node.unhandle(protocol)` / `node.getConnections(peer)` /
#   `node.getPeers()` / `node.peerStore.get(peerId)` /
#   `node.peerStore.merge(peerId, {publicKey, multiaddrs,
#   protocols, tags})` /  `node.peerStore.all(query)` /
#   `node.services.<name>` accessors for every typed service
#   (identify, ping, fetch, dcutr, autoNAT, relay, kad-dht,
#   gossipsub, pubsub-peer-discovery, etc.), the typed
#   `PeerId` / `Multiaddr` / `Stream` / `Connection` /
#   `ConnectionEncrypter` / `StreamMuxer` /
#   `Transport<DialOptions, ListenerOptions>` /
#   `PeerDiscovery<Events>` primitives, the typed Service
#   factory pattern (`services: { identify: identify(),
#   tcp: tcp(), webRTC: webRTC(), webSockets: webSockets({
#   filter: filters.all }), bootstrap: bootstrap({list:
#   [...]}), mdns: mdns(), kadDHT: kadDHT({protocol:
#   '/ipfs/kad/1.0.0', clientMode: false}), gossipsub:
#   gossipsub({ allowPublishToZeroTopicPeers: true,
#   emitSelf: false }) })`.  `helia` exposes the typed
#   `createHelia({ libp2p, blockstore, datastore,
#   blockBrokers, routers, hashers, codecs, dns, logger })`
#   factory returning a typed `Helia` node with
#   `helia.libp2p` / `helia.blockstore` / `helia.datastore` /
#   `helia.pins.add(cid, { signal })` /
#   `helia.pins.rm(cid, { signal })` /
#   `helia.pins.ls(options)` /
#   `helia.pins.isPinned(cid)` /
#   `helia.gc({ signal })` /
#   `helia.routing.findProviders(cid)` /
#   `helia.routing.provide(cid)` /
#   `helia.routing.put(key, value)` /
#   `helia.routing.get(key)` lifecycle primitives, plus the
#   add-on packages (`@helia/unixfs.addFile`,
#   `@helia/unixfs.cat`, `@helia/unixfs.ls`,
#   `@helia/unixfs.cp`, `@helia/unixfs.mkdir`,
#   `@helia/unixfs.rm`, `@helia/unixfs.stat`,
#   `@helia/block-brokers.bitswap`,
#   `@helia/block-brokers.trustlessGateway`).  filecoin-pin's
#   `src/create-pinning-helia.ts` constructs a typed `Helia`
#   instance per server boot, wires the Bitswap block broker
#   into the Filecoin storage backend via the
#   `@filoz/synapse-sdk` Synapse client, and uses
#   `helia.pins.add(cid)` / `helia.pins.rm(cid)` to expose the
#   pinning-service-API endpoints over Fastify.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/filecoin-project/filecoin-pin/contents/
#         package.json
#       → "libp2p": "^3.2.2"
#       → "helia": "^6.1.4"
#       → "@helia/unixfs": "^7.0.4"
